==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: olefine
<hw>o"le*fine</hw></mhw>
<pr>(⟦omac⟧"l⟦esl⟧*f⟦icr⟧n <it>or</it> ⟦omac⟧"l⟦esl⟧*f⟦emac⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From <er>Olefiant</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Olefiant gas, or ethylene. See
<er>Ethylene</er>.</def> <mark>[archaic]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Any one
of the series of unsaturated hydrocarbons of which ethylene is the type;
a member of the alkene series of hydrocarbons; an alkene.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oleic</ent>⟦br⟧
